{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"f9058e00-44df-11ed-8998-84c3138db4bf","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"376bb9b9-7536-48d6-8aa1-b4ca43ea99f9","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The Dividend-Discount Model","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"b940e0ff-5104-44ff-ae6e-0df6c9ae41af"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":4},"ref":"8c4111ba-3f7c-4115-b23a-9ff49db255f1","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"37700454-1bd0-49c9-b06c-25f8e9ceb5c8","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"cc69b6a9-5bc2-41b2-85c6-9b47a3033997","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume Evco, Inc., has a current stock price of $50 and will pay a $2 dividend in one year; its equity cost of capital is 15%. What price must you expect Evco stock to sell for immediat","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"e","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"object":"text","text":"ly after the firm pays the dividend in one year to justify its current price?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"86d349ab-eaca-45af-8362-3233ced7bb68","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d077e642-ec33-4b26-a08d-2a75be2dad96","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"You just purchased a share of SPCC for $100. You expect to receive a dividend of $5 in one year. If you expect the price after the dividend is paid to be $110, what total return will you have earned over the year? What was your dividend yield? Your capital gain rate?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"908929bf-ecc0-4f03-a42c-d16aaccd4de1","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"11eef6e1-e398-4358-b981-104d7250368e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume Coleco pays an annual dividend of $1.50 and has a share price of $37.50. It announces that its annual dividend will increase to $1.75. If its dividend yield is to stay the same, what should its new share price be?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"2f45a0a9-46b5-498f-b381-8ee0f3e4be9a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"29d00b68-3b89-486e-95d9-414fdebfc451","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Anle Corporation has a current stock price of $20 and is expected to pay a dividend of $1 in one year. Its expected stock price right after paying that dividend is $22.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"fa4295f8-fa85-4620-b240-14b492f6d926","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d153a3d9-a3d3-4230-abdb-5d1be23470d5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"f49c438a-ef5a-4595-8080-d8ef8714f09d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is Anle’s equity cost of capital?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"3c591955-98e4-41d8-a3ad-c0567cb6b5af","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"db2c5041-0a1a-44b4-ab08-931564ef944d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"How much of Anle’s equity cost of capital is expected to be satisfied by dividend yield and how much by capital gain?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"43043e6c-76f7-4041-898a-f908a332761d","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"c6e76b56-2b99-4cdf-a83d-697d9ed5f235","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Achi Corp. has preferred stock with an annual dividend of $3. If the required return on Achi’s preferred stock is 8%, what is its price? (","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"Hint","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":": For a preferred stock, the dividend growth rate is zero.)","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"8f4c1657-7074-42a6-9d36-ddd74bcfec5a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"cb52d44b-cecd-4da0-8a5c-9c030ef61224","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Ovit, Inc., has preferred stock with a price of $20 and a dividend of $1.50 per year. What is its dividend yield?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"831a5958-f8a6-492d-9454-983fff3c576d"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":{"$ambrosia":"aero:asset:upload","urn":"urn:aero:4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","asset":{"urn":"urn:aero:4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"a00ebe86-c3c5-4c8e-972b-e4383e44477f","name":"Excel.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998380,"lastSyncDate":1665085941},"source":{"thumb":{"width":272,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/thumb/a00f1074293d56498c15895ac72ddbca.jpeg","height":150},"original":{"width":67,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/4ab45a10-44e0-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c/original/a00f1074293d56498c15895ac72ddbca.jpeg","height":37}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"Excel.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"37"}}},"alt":"","caption":"","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"","activityTitle":""},"height":37,"ref":"cadd12d9-e24c-47c8-b578-6ee1770b674d"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":10},"ref":"eda81cfc-f4d5-43a3-857d-78414635ff33","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"77a9116d-8278-4376-a19d-d798992b405f","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"3f42ac40-ff05-490a-91d8-26abbe6fa272","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose Acap Corporation will pay a dividend of $2.80 per share at the end of this year and a dividend of $3 per share next year. You expect Acap’s stock price to be $52 in two years. Assume that Acap’s equity cost of capital is 10%.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"e94d3e6e-2f7d-4e48-b50d-bd690fd29a5a","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"8e304591-e0cd-471c-95d4-572913be9c15","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"6243d06a-bd7e-492c-a342-0acb767900e2","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What price would you be willing to pay for a share of Acap stock today, if you planned to hold the stock for two years?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"52018765-e193-4d82-86fc-d38a7f3b10f7","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"8b3ac6c4-6687-4b64-8c34-a3f052c36abc","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose instead you plan to hold the stock for one year. For what price would you expect to be able to sell a share of Acap stock in one year?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d440fd80-e378-4cc9-ba2f-d4dbd62526a6","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"7571ca5a-0b77-486a-8abb-f19ef3d725e0","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Given your answer to (b), what price would you be willing to pay for a share of Acap stock today, if you planned to hold the stock for one year? How does this price compare to your answer in (a)?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"b878d74d-be75-4e2f-807d-0d5b2bd2eb88","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e7e28264-fc6e-41c5-b90b-5812375ee849","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Krell Industries has a share price of $22.00 today. If Krell is expected to pay a dividend of $0.88 this year and its stock price is expected to grow to $23.54 at the end of the year, what is Krell’s dividend yield and equity cost of capital?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"faf3e8ab-8f64-4144-a226-6f0b1ebecd08"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"